So, this NPR story has a quote by a former Meta exec.

https://www.npr.org/2023/10/21/1207795093/ceo-of-web-summit-tech-conference-resigns-over-israel-comments

And this Fortune article has a lot of confirmations by different organisations:

https://fortune.com/2023/10/20/web-summit-google-meta-stripe-pull-out-israel-hamas-gaza/

OK, this one has some actual quotes.

https://www.theregister.com/2023/10/20/web_summit_cancelations_israel/

They're mostly just, "We pulled out", though.

Bleah.. feeling like the Time Capsule (2TB model from 2013) is wanting replacement at some point - had to reset it about three times in the past week. Still works otherwise, but, hardly reliably. Thinking an old Mac mini (2015 or so) should be cheap enough to use as a replacement, with the bonus of being able to pick a recent WiFi dongle, and for Apple SoftRAID support, so the photography backups could be connected. Maybe I'll try setting up the old MBP in that role, as a test, to verify everything actually works with the concept. Could also get some nice adblocking in place at the same time - another layer of junk removal never hurts.
